g.aria-label: splitwith(Pred, L) -> splitwith(Pred, L, []). splitwith(Pred, [H|T], L) -> case Pred(H) of true -> splitwith(Pred, T, [H|L]); false -> {reverse(L), [H|T]} end; splitwith(Pred, [], L) -> {reverse(L), []}. splitwith(P, L) splits the list L into the two sub-lists fL1, L2g, where L = takewhile(P, L) and L2 = dropwhile(P, L). > lists:splitwith(Big, [200,500,45,5,3,45,6]). f[200,500,45],[5,3,45,6]g
